        "goal_understanding": "The goal of the game is to navigate through a grid and complete all goal cells by stepping on them while the player's piece simultaneously matches the goal's required shape, color, and rotation. The game is won by completing all goals across all levels.",
        "mechanics_understanding": "The game uses a turn-based grid movement system. Each move costs 1 stamina; stamina reaching 0 causes a life loss and resets stamina. Losing all lives ends the game. Walls block movement\u2014repeatedly trying a blocked direction wastes stamina. Modifier tiles on the grid alter the piece's attributes: shape modifiers cycle the shape (0\u20135), color modifiers cycle through orange\u2192blue\u2192green\u2192red\u2192orange, and rotation modifiers rotate the piece 90\u00b0 clockwise. A goal becomes activated only when the piece's current shape, color, and rotation all match the goal's requirements; then stepping onto that goal cell completes it. Effective play requires planning a route to collect necessary modifiers before reaching the goal, while avoiding blocked directions and managing stamina."
